title: Tension in Tennant Creek as Govt launches inquiry into Aboriginal corporation
text: The Federal Government's decision to launch an inquiry into one of the Northern Territory's largest Aboriginal corporations has increased divisions and tensions in the remote town of Tennant Creek. The Prime Minister's department is looking into the Julalikari Council Aboriginal Corporation's compliance with federal funding programs following complaints from residents. ...
